            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=pog",
                        "name": "pog",
                        "displayName": "Jan Juricek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi. This behaviour occurs when you're trying to add an action to unknown controller. \n\nTry to use this command (with small I letter in controller name):\n\nzf.bat create action send index\n\nIt should work. \n\nMy bugtrack:\n\nZend_Tool_Project_Provider_Action::hasResource()\n\ncontains :\n\n$controllerFile = self::_getControllerFileResource($profile, $controllerName, $moduleName);\n\nnow, when you specify unknown controller, it returns false, as defined in Zend_Tool_Project_Profile_Resource_Container::find(). It should definitely either throw a warning, if the $controllerFile === false saying it's case sensitive, maybe explain it a little bit. Maybe it could be good to try to lower the first letter in the find() function before giving up the controller search...\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=pog",
                        "name": "pog",
                        "displayName": "Jan Juricek",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-30T09:15:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-30T09:15:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31551",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsv",
                        "name": "lsv",
                        "displayName": "Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually i have switched to zf.sh, and in the controller help, there stands you shouldnt add controller name if you are adding actions to the index controller.\nIm not sure if this also stands in the zf.bat file.\n\nBut yes, a bit nicer error would be a great addition.\n\nAlso in zf.sh, it works with both lower- and uppercase controller name \/ action names...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lsv",
                        "name": "lsv",
                        "displayName": "Martin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-02T07:11:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-02T07:11:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
